    "body": "**Recovery with seed phrase**\r\n\r\n1. The toolbar is too big. It supposed to have a fixed height, just as on any other screens of the app\r\n<img width=\"868\" alt=\"64331469-8654c280-cfdb-11e9-84ed-98f57b05dbe5\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1019573/64334442-38db5400-cfe1-11e9-8f00-9a467222286d.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n2. There are some layout issues and i've added some minor design changes\r\n<img width=\"1202\" alt=\"64332777-d3399880-cfdd-11e9-8f49-6e10c9f7ccc9\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1019573/64334485-4ee91480-cfe1-11e9-815f-db6f1e58ac5d.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n- There's not a top border in the toolbar, just like in the onboarding flow;\r\n- The description text, explaining the number of words the user has to enter is aligned to the bottom and has an 8px margin between it and the toolbar;\r\n- The word count now has \"Word count:\" prefix. It is invisible when there has been no words entered yet, has a green check icon in a semi-transparent green circle when the word count matches the required number of words and is also aligned to the bottom and has an 8 px bottom margin;\r\n- The error message has one line and does not cover the title;\r\n- The words are vertically aligned in the middle between the screen title and the description text;\r\n\r\n3. The above is true for the \"re-encrypting with password\" screens, which come after the successful seed phrase recovery: top bar, toolbar, alignment;\r\n\r\n4. \"Re-encrypt your key\" button's bottom margins seem not to be 16px which it should (not sure);\r\n\r\n5. \"Welcome to status\" screen has a broken icon in it and is shown not long enough, there should be enough time to read the text on it.",
